<h3>Data Down, Actions Up</h3>
<hr>
<div class="row">
  <div class="col-xs-12 col-sm-3 col-lg-3">
    {{ui-buttons
      cardinality='1:2'
      buttons='Foo,Bar,Baz'
      defaultValue='bar'
      changed="changed"
      action="action"
      error="error"
      disabled=d2
      registration="registration"
    }}<br/>
    <p class="downer">values: {{actionValues}}</p>  </div>
    <div class="flashy">
      {{#each flashMessages.queue as |flash|}}
        {{flash-message flash=flash}}
      {{/each}}
    </div>
  <div class="col-xs-12 col-sm-3 col-lg-4 monospace">
  <b>\{{ui-buttons </b><br/>
  &nbsp;&nbsp;buttons='Foo,Bar,Baz' <br/>
  &nbsp;&nbsp;cardinality='1:2'<br/>
  &nbsp;&nbsp;disabled={{d2}}<br/>
  &nbsp;&nbsp;changed="changed"<br/>
  &nbsp;&nbsp;action="action"<br/>
  &nbsp;&nbsp;error="error"<br/>
  &nbsp;&nbsp;registration="registration"<br/>
  }}
  <br/>
  {{ui-toggle-button on='enable foo' off='disable foo' onValue='foo' offValue=false value=d2}}
  </div>
  <div class="col-xs-4 col-sm-5 col-lg-5">
    Actions available include (see diagram below for visual representation):
    <ul>
      <li><b>action</b> - the default action which gets the majority of the actions sent to it (blue flash msgs).</li>
      <li><b>changed</b> - fires only when the "values" or "disabled" property changes (green flash msgs).</li>
      <li><b>error</b> - if any warning/error conditions happen -- like running into a cardinality constraint -- this is fired</li>
      <li><b>registration</b> - indicates when buttons register with the group and when the group is completed with registration</li>
    </ul>
  </div>
</div>

<h3>Shortcut Components</h3>
<hr>
<div class="row">
  <div class="col-xs-12 col-sm-3 col-lg-3">
    {{radio-buttons
      buttons='Foo,Bar,Baz'
      value=radioValue
    }}<br/>
    <p class="downer">value: {{radioValue}}</p>  </div>
  <div class="col-xs-12 col-sm-3 col-lg-4 monospace">
  <b>\{{radio-buttons </b><br/>
  &nbsp;&nbsp;buttons='Foo,Bar,Baz' <br/>
  }}
  </div>
  <div class="col-xs-12 col-sm-5 col-lg-5">
    <h4>Radio Buttons</h4>
    A simple shortcut/config for ui-buttons ... this simply sets the default
    cardinality to a default of '1:1'. While this example is <i>inline</i> it
    could just as easily be used in a block form.
    <br/>
    <note>
      <b>Note:</b> because the cardinality <i>requires</i> that at least 1 button be selected you'll see that "Foo" button becomes active even though we didn't state a <prop>value</prop> or a <prop>defaultValue</prop>
    </note>
  </div>
</div>
<div class="row">
  <div class="col-xs-12 col-sm-3 col-lg-3">
    {{checkbox-buttons
      buttons='Foo,Bar,Baz'
      values=checkValue
    }}<br/>
    <p class="downer">values: {{checkValue}}</p>  </div>
  <div class="col-xs-3 col-sm-3 col-lg-4 monospace">
  <b>\{{checkbox-buttons </b><br/>
  &nbsp;&nbsp;buttons='Foo,Bar,Baz' <br/>
  }}
  </div>
  <div class="col-xs-12 col-sm-5 col-lg-5">
    <h4>Checkbox Buttons</h4>
    Another simple shortcut/config ... this  sets the default cardinality to '0:M'
  </div>
</div>

